<section id="voucherItemDistrib">
  <title><indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>vouchers</primary>
      <secondary>splitting receipts for</secondary>
    </indexterm> <indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>receipts</primary>
      <secondary>splitting at vouchering</secondary>
    </indexterm> Split Receipt</title>
  <para>To split a Purchase Order Receipt into different quantities, select
  the "Split Receipt" option from the right-click menu. The following screen
  will appear:</para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/splitReceipt.png" />
        </imageobject>
        <caption>Splitting Voucher Item Receipt</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para>When splitting a Receipt quantity, you are presented with the
  following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Order Number</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Line #</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Date Received</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Qty. Received</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Qty. Split</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Freight</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Freight Split</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>To the far right of the screen, the following buttons are
  available:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>CANCEL</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the previous screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>SPLIT</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>